data.text:
Phantom Lady is a 1944 American FILM NOlR directed by Robert Siodmak and starring Franchot Tone, Ella Raines, and Alan Curtis. IThe film was Siodmak's first Hollywood noir and was based on the novel of the same name written by Cornell Woolrich but published under the pseudonym William Irish.

You can find out more about this movie from Wikipedia and read an article from FILM NOlR of the Week. A detailed article from online blog Film Noir Board may still be available.
